================================================================================
A note on SHA pins
================================================================================

Every third-party action above is pinned to a full 40-character commit SHA with a
trailing `# vX.Y.Z` comment in the workflow files, rather than a mutable tag. This
mirrors the practice observed most consistently among Scorecard-adopting repos in
the Google sample (docs/research/google.md) and is intended to prevent a
compromised or force-pushed tag from silently changing what code your CI runs.
When bumping a pin, re-resolve the tag to its current commit SHA rather than
trusting a cached value — tags are not immutable on GitHub.
